docs.lead_paragraph: NEWS GATHERINGS.--During the past week there were 418 deaths in this city, as follows; Men, 91; Women, 88; Boys, 148; Girls, 91; of those 62 died of Consumption, 36 from Inflammation of the Lungs, 6 from Congestion of the Lungs, 10 from Scarlet Fever, 24 from Typhus Fever, 11 from Small Pox, and 39 from Convulsions.

docs.lead_paragraph: A notice from his Excellency, Prince Schwarzenburg, informs mankind that foreigners are not to be permitted hereafter the privilege of free ingress and regress from the Austrian dominions.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Baptist Recorder announces that Rev. R. R. Raymond of Syracuse, has resigned the pastoral charge of the congregation over which he has heretofore presided in that city; also, that he is to become associated with the New-York Daily Times, as literary Editor. This error has evidently arisen from the fact, that the Rev. gentleman referred to is expected to assume the editorial management of a daily paper about to be established at Syracuse.
